name: Mt Davis
comments: Mount Davis is the highest point in Pennsylvania. Located in the 5,685-acre Forbes State Forest near the hamlet of Markleton in Elk Lick Township, Somerset County, it lies on a gentle crest of a 30-mile ridge line extending from central Somerset County southward into Garrett County, Maryland known as Negro Mountain.
